"{\"uid\": \"inews.co.uk-sport-olympics-olympic-running-track-purple-paris-2024-3191070\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"IMPARTIAL NEWS + INTELLIGENT DEBATE  Account  Team GB's runners will be pounding a bright lavender circuit containing seashells - here's why  TheParis 2024 Olympicshave almost arrived.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 184, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"TheOpening Ceremonywill take place this evening, with diverTom Daleyand rowerHelen Gloverthe flag bearers for Team GB.\", \"from\": 185, \"to\": 303, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 295, \"end\": 302, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999999999959073, \"rank\": 4.261706251399042e-12, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The British team will be represented by 327 athletes, across a range of disciplines, all hoping to bring home a coveted medal.\", \"from\": 305, \"to\": 431, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 309, \"end\": 316, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.8930744683661352, \"rank\": 0.11872097776425238, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Competitors from England, Scotland, Wales and Northern Ireland are all taking part.\", \"from\": 433, \"to\": 516, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 450, \"end\": 457, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.7370594890985045, \"rank\": 0.35624037415232807, \"text\": \"England\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 459, \"end\": 467, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scotland\", \"score\": 0.9767449959687405, \"rank\": 0.023216715038642876, \"text\": \"Scotland\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scotland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scotland\"}, {\"begin\": 469, \"end\": 474, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wales\", \"score\": 0.9995483396004429, \"rank\": 0.00044597139707602416, \"text\": \"Wales\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wales\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wales\"}, {\"begin\": 479, \"end\": 495, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Northern_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999981273971824, \"rank\": 1.8725848740464272e-06, \"text\": \"Northern Ireland\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Northern_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Northern_Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The athletics contingent this year includesDina Asher-Smith,Katarina Johnson-Thompson, Sam Atkin, Jeremiah Azu and Emile Cairess.\", \"from\": 518, \"to\": 647, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 578, \"end\": 603, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katarina_Johnson-Thompson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katarina Johnson-Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katarina_Johnson-Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katarina_Johnson-Thompson\"}, {\"begin\": 605, \"end\": 614, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Atkin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sam Atkin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Atkin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Atkin\"}, {\"begin\": 616, \"end\": 628, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeremiah_Azu\", \"score\": 0.9999990537371489, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jeremiah Azu\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeremiah_Azu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeremiah_Azu\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Asher-Smith is looking to become the first British woman to claim Olympic sprint gold in either the 100m or 200m, while marathon runner Caireses finished third at this year'sLondon Marathonin a remarkable time of just 2:06:46, making him the second-fastest British marathoner ever.\", \"from\": 649, \"to\": 930, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 692, \"end\": 699, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.8930744683661352, \"rank\": 0.11872097776425238, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Speaking of her ambitions at this year's games, Asher-Smith seems confident.\", \"from\": 932, \"to\": 1008, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am running great,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 1009, \"to\": 1040, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am happy that as we are coming into the crunch time in the season everything's coming together.\", \"from\": 1041, \"to\": 1139, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am on track.\", \"from\": 1140, \"to\": 1154, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I want to be so successful, I want to do myself proud and I want to create history.\", \"from\": 1156, \"to\": 1240, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's not my first rodeo and I am very excited going into my third Olympic Games in a really good place.\\\"\", \"from\": 1241, \"to\": 1345, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Viewers may be used to seeing Olympic running tracks in a rust-red hue, but in Paris, athletes can look forward to competing on a purple track.\", \"from\": 1347, \"to\": 1490, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1426, \"end\": 1431, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 2.7512600715058797e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Alain Blondel, sports manager in charge of athletics for Paris 2024, said the decision was a creative one.\", \"from\": 1492, \"to\": 1598, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1492, \"end\": 1505, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alain_Blondel\", \"score\": 0.9999990810651654, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alain Blondel\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alain_Blondel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alain_Blondel\"}, {\"begin\": 1549, \"end\": 1559, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1269243566173198e-19, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The big part of the job was to come up with a track that was different from what we had seen, to maintain the creative approach that the Organising Committee has had since it was set up, to go a little bit outside the box,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 1600, \"to\": 1833, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The look of the Games includes three colours for all the competition venues: blue, green and purple.\", \"from\": 1835, \"to\": 1936, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We decided on this purple track with different tones: lighter for the track, darker for the service areas, and grey for the turns at the end of the bend, reminding of the ash-coloured tracks that were there 100 years ago for the Olympic Games Paris 1924.\\\"\", \"from\": 1937, \"to\": 2192, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Who else than Carl Lewis to unveil our purple track \\ud83d\\udc9cThe Stade de France is more than ready for the Athletics event this summer.\", \"from\": 2194, \"to\": 2322, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2208, \"end\": 2218, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carl Lewis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Be ready, this track will be faaaast \\u26a1pic.twitter.com/cmxzDaVIzH  He added: \\\"We had to work hard on the colours, so that they came out in the best possible tones to highlight the athletes.\", \"from\": 2323, \"to\": 2511, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's a track, it has to be pretty, but above all it's a stage on which the athletes are going to perform.\", \"from\": 2513, \"to\": 2619, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What's really important is that the colours and the athletes stand out.\\\"\", \"from\": 2620, \"to\": 2692, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tony Estanguet, president of Paris 2024, said this year's Olympic aesthetic comprised elegance, creativity and the \\\"French art de vivre\\\".\", \"from\": 2694, \"to\": 2831, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2695, \"end\": 2709, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tony Estanguet\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\"}, {\"begin\": 2724, \"end\": 2734, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1269243566173198e-19, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2811, \"end\": 2817, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.6625594028178758, \"rank\": 0.4636795126311753, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The purple track intends to convey a \\\"joyful and festive tone\\\", he added.\", \"from\": 2833, \"to\": 2906, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was designed by Italian company Mondo, which has been responsible for every Olympic track since 1976.\", \"from\": 2908, \"to\": 3012, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2928, \"end\": 2935, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"score\": 0.998521587338569, \"rank\": 0.0014559002904371184, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2944, \"end\": 2949, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mondo_Media\", \"score\": 0.9838833905616808, \"rank\": 0.01630890304513712, \"text\": \"Mondo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mondo_Media\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mondo_Media\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With Paris 2024 aiming to bethe most sustainable Summer Games ever, Mondo has incorporated some unusual natural materials in their track.\", \"from\": 3014, \"to\": 3151, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3020, \"end\": 3030, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1269243566173198e-19, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 3083, \"end\": 3088, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mondo_Media\", \"score\": 0.9838833905616808, \"rank\": 0.01630890304513712, \"text\": \"Mondo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mondo_Media\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mondo_Media\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These include the shells of bivalve molluscs, such as clams and mussels, which contain calcium carbonate, a substance often used in resilient flooring.\", \"from\": 3153, \"to\": 3304, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The shells are cleaned and ground into a powder to use in the tracks.\", \"from\": 3306, \"to\": 3375, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Alessandro Piceli, a research and development manager at Mondo, claims that their current purple iteration is even better than that used at the 2020 Tokyo Games.\", \"from\": 3377, \"to\": 3538, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3435, \"end\": 3440, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mondo_Media\", \"score\": 0.9838833905616808, \"rank\": 0.01630890304513712, \"text\": \"Mondo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mondo_Media\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mondo_Media\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We are focusing on the dynamic connection between the track and a new generation of shoes,\\\" he toldThe Guardian.\", \"from\": 3540, \"to\": 3653, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"For the track, we only see the aesthetics, but there is great work that goes into the underlayer.\", \"from\": 3655, \"to\": 3753, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"A new granule of polymeric material, made especially for it, was inserted in the Tokyo track.\", \"from\": 3755, \"to\": 3849, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3838, \"end\": 3843, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9997595011253136, \"rank\": 0.0002405564681995891, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We have made it even better now.\", \"from\": 3850, \"to\": 3882, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We have chemists, engineers and physicists who take care of the performance of the material.\", \"from\": 3883, \"to\": 3975, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"When it comes to running tracks, red is a popular colour as it is the most UV stable, meaning it is more resistant to fading in the sunlight.\", \"from\": 3975, \"to\": 4117, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Green and blue are also desirable choices as these are less prone to wearing and fading.\", \"from\": 4119, \"to\": 4207, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Most running tracks are made from a multilayered system composed of rubber andplastic.\", \"from\": 4209, \"to\": 4295, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Historically, they were constructed from rubber and asphalt, while some incorporated sand or even hay.\", \"from\": 4297, \"to\": 4399, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 1960s saw the arrival of polyurethane surfaces.\", \"from\": 4401, \"to\": 4452, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Mexico City Olympics in 1968 marked the first time a synthetic system was used at an international track-and-field event.\", \"from\": 4453, \"to\": 4578, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4458, \"end\": 4469, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1968_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999990423021, \"rank\": 9.577427837578867e-10, \"text\": \"Mexico City\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1968_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1968_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletes of a certain age may also know running tracks as \\\"tartan\\\" - the name that US company 3M gave to the polyurethane floor it developed for the 1968 Games.\", \"from\": 4580, \"to\": 4740, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4664, \"end\": 4666, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999909418171302, \"rank\": 8.209917104750278e-06, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While 3M stopped making the track material decades ago, the term \\\"tartan\\\" endures in the sporting lexicon.\", \"from\": 4742, \"to\": 4848, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Impartial news + intelligent debate  All rights reserved.\", \"from\": 4850, \"to\": 4907, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a9 2026 Associated Newspapers Limited.\", \"from\": 4908, \"to\": 4945, \"entities\": []}]}"